OL,3,C'I can walk away', says council leader
OL,4,Cafter Reform UK expulsion
OL,6,FCooper has not addressed these
OL,7,Fspecific allegations publicly.
OL,9,FNine Labour MPs across Staffordshire
OL,10,Fand Stoke have urged him to resign
OL,11,Fboth as council leader and councillor,
OL,12,Fsaying he has "exposed his far-right
OL,13,Fand racist opinions."
OL,15,FStaffordshire Conservatives also
OL,16,Fcriticised Reform UK's handling of the
OL,17,Fsituation. Their group leader, Cllr
OL,18,FPhilip White, said Cooper's removal
OL,19,Fwas "inevitable" but argued the wider
OL,20,Fissues within the party locally were
OL,21,Fbeing "swept under the carpet."
